DETAIL is a parameterized expense detail report. It accepts an optional PARAM.category — when provided, only expenses in that category are returned; when blank, every expense is returned. Results are ordered by transaction date descending and emitted as pipe-delimited text with a header row (DATE|CATEGORY|COMPANY|DETAIL|AMOUNT|STATE|SUBMITTER). The program is published as a public report and is the primary input to the /export-report flow that generates CSV, JSON, PDF, and XLSX downloads. Called by the expense tracker frontend's Export page and by anyone hitting /report?name=DETAIL directly.
